21 WHEREAS, the 69th Legislature affirms the intent of the 42nd Legislature, which expressed the
22 following statements and positions while passing MEPA into law in 1971: "A major conservation challenge
23 today is to achieve needed development and use of our natural resources while concurrently protecting and
24 enhancing the quality of our environment. MEPA seeks that often elusive middle ground between purely
25 preservationist philosophy and purely exploitive philosophy, and indeed we must soon find that middle ground.
26 As we guide Montana's development, we must use scientific, technological, and sociological expertise."
